<br>
One on one I just mez them first and try and get some aid. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
In Caledonia, just had a funny one. Mezed some lackys, then all 4 of us got mezed by a cleric (revealing himself as such, we didn't know before). He set about nuking and then one of our assasins got him from behind and we revived and wiped out there group. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Was a right picture.<br>
<br>
The thing with clerics is they usually are highlanders and usually wear flashy colours. *shrug* Tends to be easy to spot them anyway. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/uentrea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Entrea</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(6/11/02 9:57:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Hmm Cleric here</span><hr size=1> My main Character is a cleric. And he is fully rej. I love being the one holding 8 people alive, ya know? I have my skald to lvl 10 now, and have been reading about them alot. Now I reconize the reason I almost never die to skalds. Alot of them are afraid to atatck a cleric fearing that cleric to be smite specced.  Now that I've read these posts, I have decided to take my respeccing options to try out smite for a while.<br>
I can't wait to get my skald to a higher lvl. So far it's been as fun as my cleric. I like the option to fight and be support.<br>
Lvl 10 Skald<br>
Merlin (With the largest pop, its easy to ask people my way around a new realm, and im loving it) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/urardils.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rardils</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/8/02 11:21:54 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm Cleric here</span><hr size=1> Scenario #1. When you get the jump on a cleric:<br>
<br>
Skald: DD1, DD2, Snare.<br>
Cleric: PBAE mez<br>
Skald: Purge, Mez, DD1, DD2<br>
Cleric: Melee/Runs<br>
Skald: Continue beatdown<br>
<br>
Scenario #2. When the cleric gets the jump on you:<br>
Cleric: Stun<br>
Skald: Purge, Spririt Bolstering Song<br>
Cleric: Nuke<br>
Skald: Run away<br>
<br>
However if you pay attention you will never be jumped by a Cleric. And when you've run away, rest up and return, commence scenario #1.<br>
<br>
/Rardils 50 Troll Skald of Merlin<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ueregil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eregil</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.iol.it/okandrea/Eregil.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/9/02 6:23:25 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.iol.it/okandrea/ereliz.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm Cleric here</span><hr size=1> Why is it that everytime I solo a cleric he/she has always both of their insta heals and this with druids too? <p><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="http://users.iol.it/okandrea/EreNi.gif"></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=ashval>Ashval</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/9/02 6:29:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm Cleric here</span><hr size=1> When I fight clerics solo (Which I find myself doing alot) I will never use Purge on thier mez. The reason behind this is if the decide to mez you and back off after there first cast just sprint at them and before the get the 2nd one off you can DD them and interupt and kill them.<br>
<br>
You will want to keep the purge ready when he decides to stun you.<br>
<br>
I did this last night with one... he intialy stuned me.. purged that and started to wack on him (saving my DD's). Then he mezed me.. backed of and started to nuke.. after the first nuke a sprinted towards him and hit him with a dd about half way through his cast.. and started wacking again.. he did have 2 of his instaheals he used and i still beat him. Was a yellow con. <p>Ashval 4X Kobald Skald -- Iseult</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ueregil.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eregil</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://users.iol.it/okandrea/Eregil.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/10/02 4:38:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.iol.it/okandrea/ereliz.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm Cleric here</span><hr size=1> Yellow con, as I have found out has a lot of variances. Basically it means he/she could be from 46 to 50 to me.<br>
<br>
If they are 46 I can take anyone down with ease, if they are 50 it takes more planning.<br>
<br>
Basically, the first thing I look for is if my opponent is wearing epic armour before I decide on the course of action. Not fool prof by has saved me a few times now. <p><IMG BORDER="0" SRC="http://users.libero.it/okandrea/EreNi.gif"></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ukethen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kethen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/11/02 9:44:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm Cleric here</span><hr size=1> Former Smite heavy/Balanced (whatever they are called now) cleric here.<br>
<br>
Just to give you guys some perspective, the mez is the life blood of a clerics one on one ability.  without the mez we can rarely get the stun off (which leads into the nuking phase), and my worst enemies were skalds.  Skalds have the speed to close the distance of 1350 range very very quickly meaning we usually cant get a smite or stun(1000 range) off before a skald is in range to interupt us with an instant, meaning that our only hope against a skald is the mez.  the only problem being is that if we do not have the time to stop and stun/nuke/nuke/nuke after the mez due to purge, resists, allies, etc. then the most we are going to be able to due is run away and try to get off the radar for a sec and come back.  <br>
Clerics run everytime when mez is purged?...i don't doubt that, not in the least.  Cleric melee (missing those all important +to hit styles) is far overrated even with the damage add when compared to a skalds 2handed+damage add.  even with both instants (which means no 48 spec smite btw), the melee of a skald vs a cleric is usually not a contest at all and without a quickcast or a mez that is all there is to use barring the PB damage (which is marginally comparable in damage to one of a skalds even though it is AE)<br>
<br>
one on one without mez the cleric will go down 90% of the time (or if the skald purges the stun, fear the stun not the mez)  <br>
<br>
Its all a chain, if jumped you must (MUST) mez/stun/nuke/nuke/nuke<br>
or mez/nuke/stun/nuke/nuke/nuke &lt;--(not vs any instant casters or your screwed)<br>
attempting to melee is usually a futile attempt, and it all goes back to the &quot;if i can catch them with a stun&quot;...<br>
<br>
skalds were usually one of my most feared opponents so the feeling goes both ways <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
of course now I am a skald on Mordred and loving every minute of it.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=saebjorn>Saebjorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/16/02 6:00:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm Cleric here</span><hr size=1> If u get close enough when he starts nukeing u, when ur stunned, spam the mezz button, he will be mezzed as soon as u break the stun, now rest and use all the stuff u can to raise your hp, end or power back, then go DD+DD+best style him.<br>
<br>
And try to save your DD's till he has like 10% left, then he is about to insta heal, u DD 2 and hit him, and he's dead. Try to get spirit reist as high as u can, with 24% and 46% with the chant on, they hardly can mez me, I resist all the time<br>
<br>
Saebjorn Oskarsson the lvl 50 skald <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#ff0000>- </font><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald>Team Skald</a><font color=#ff0000> - </font><a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm10>RvR Discussions</a><font color=#ff0000> - </font> <!-- #EndEditable -->
